├── utils.py            # Shared utilities
│
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py         # FastAPI app — /chat and /scorecard endpoints
│   ├── requirements.txt
│   └── Procfile        # Railway deploy config
│
└── frontend/
    ├── index.html
    ├── vite.config.js
    ├── package.json
    └── src/
        ├── main.jsx
        └── App.jsx     # Full application — landing, auth, interview, scorecard
```

---

## Prompt Engineering

This project started as an exploration of prompting techniques. Five distinct system prompt strategies are implemented and selectable at runtime:

| Technique | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| **Zero-Shot** | Direct questions, no scaffolding. Tests raw reasoning. |
| **Few-Shot** | Illustrates expectations with examples before asking. |
| **Chain-of-Thought** | Prompts the candidate to think aloud step by step. |
| **Role-Based** | AI embodies a named senior hiring manager persona. |
| **Structured** | Requests STAR-format responses explicitly. |

Each technique uses the same base model but produces measurably different question styles, follow-up depth, and feedback tone — which is the point.

---

## Running Locally

**Prerequisites:** Node.js 18+, Python 3.9+, an OpenAI API key

```bash
# Clone
git clone https://github.com/your-username/nous-ai.git
cd nous-ai

# Backend
cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000

# Frontend (new terminal)
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open `http://localhost:5173`, enter your OpenAI key in the sidebar, and start practising.

---

## API Endpoints

```
POST /chat
  Body: { api_key, messages, context, mode, level, technique }
  Returns: { message, tokens: { input, output }, cost }

POST /scorecard
  Body: { api_key, messages, mode, level }
  Returns: { overall, competencies[], strengths[], improvements[] }

GET /
  Returns: { status: "NOUS AI backend running" }
```

---

## Deploying

**Backend → Railway**
1. New project → Deploy from GitHub → set root directory to `backend`
2. Railway detects the Procfile automatically
3. Generate a domain under Settings → Networking

**Frontend → Vercel**
1. Import repo → set root directory to `frontend`
2. Add environment variable: `VITE_API_URL=https://your-railway-url.railway.app`
3. Deploy

